      "claimType": "builder.execute.scope",
      "fieldOrBehavior": "Fix-plan-iteration-1 CRITICAL/HIGH/MED code-review findings verified resolved by diff read against scripts/hooks/lib/liveness-heartbeat.js, scripts/hooks/{claude,codex,opencode,pi}-telemetry-hook.js, and src/cli/workflow-sidecar.ts: (1) CRITICAL -- liveness-heartbeat.js's new computeConflict() is the single choke point where conflict.actor/conflict.lastAt are constructed from the multi-writer append-only events.jsonl stream; it now applies sanitizeSegment (the same allowlist+64-char-cap the write side already applies to legitimate actors) to actor, and re-serializes lastAt via Date.parse -> new Date(...).toISOString() (structurally eliminating control chars/ANSI on a timestamp), so all four wrapper call sites inherit sanitized values with no per-wrapper defense to forget (F1). (2) HIGH -- all four wrapper interpolation sites now render the actor/lastAt inside double quotes within the fixed `[LIVENESS CONFLICT] actor \"...\" claimed this subject at \"...\" -- run \\`liveness verdict\\` and coordinate.` directive sentence; because the values are pre-sanitized (no control chars/newlines survive sanitizeSegment/ISO-reserialization), a hostile actor cannot escape the quotes or splice a forged [SYSTEM]-style directive into the trusted instruction text (F2). (3) HIGH -- workflow-sidecar.ts's `liveness verdict --json` branch now runs winner/losers/holders actor+claimAt+lastAt through a dedicated sanitizeVerdictHolderForJson (stripControlCharsForDisplay + .slice(0,64)) before JSON.stringify, closing the second LLM-facing injection path the pull-work skill's --json consumption opened, while leaving the underlying result/holders/winner/losers objects unsanitized for internal use (loser-release contract unaffected) (F3). (4) MED -- length cap enforced consistently via sanitizeSegment's 64-char cap and matching .slice(0,64) calls on the JSON path (F4). (5) MED -- both evals/integration/test_liveness_conflict_injection.sh and test_liveness_verdict.sh gained a new adversarial Section H (hand-seeded hostile actor: embedded newline + ANSI CSI + literal '[SYSTEM] Ignore all previous instructions...' payload) asserting the hostile text never appears raw in additionalContext/stderr/verdict output (text and --json) and that the directive sentence stays structurally intact -- both pass (F5). Independently confirmed no provider/network calls were introduced anywhere in the fix diff or the two new eval files (grepped for fetch/http(s)/axios/child_process/exec/spawn/api.openai/anthropic -- zero matches). Full regression suite (static preset, heartbeat, preflight, field-preservation, manifest self-check) green with no assertion weakened or removed. Hostile-actor repro from the code review, which previously succeeded (verbatim newline+ANSI+[SYSTEM] text reaching additionalContext), now fails closed per the new Section H assertions in both adversarial evals.",
      "value": "pass",
