      "excerptOrSummary": "ACCEPTED GAP, not a defect, carried over unchanged: opencode's and pi's generated plugin/extension do not consume ANY telemetry-wrapper stdout today, so the mid-turn conflict signal cannot be obeyed live on those two runtimes -- only the disclosed stderr diagnostic plus the next-turn workflow-steering.js digest fallback are real there. Disclosed in the plan's Unresolved Questions #1, docs/workflow-usage-guide.md's Mid-flight row (follow-up #333), and the Definition Of Done's explicit exclusion list. Unaffected by this security-fix iteration (the stderr diagnostic itself is now sanitized -- see liveness-conflict-injection-integration Section H -- but the underlying live-obedience gap on opencode/pi is unchanged). approved_by: brian.anderson1222@gmail.com (session-approved).",
