      "claimId": "kontourai-flow-agents-320-security-fix-injection-remediation-iter1.flow-agents-workflow.fix-plan-iteration-1-critical-high-med-code-review-findings-verified-resolved-by-diff-read-against-scripts-hooks-lib-liveness-heartbeat-js-scripts-hooks-claude-codex-opencode-pi-telemetry-hook-js-and-src-cli-workflow-sidecar-ts-1-critical-liveness-heartbeat-js-s-new-computeconflict-is-the-single-choke-point-where-conflict-actor-conflict-lastat-are-constructed-from-the-multi-writer-append-only-events-jsonl-stream-it-now-applies-sanitizesegment-the-same-allowlist-64-char-cap-the-write-side-already-applies-to-legitimate-actors-to-actor-and-re-serializes-lastat-via-date-parse-new-date-toisostring-structurally-eliminating-control-chars-ansi-on-a-timestamp-so-all-four-wrapper-call-sites-inherit-sanitized-values-with-no-per-wrapper-defense-to-forget-f1-2-high-all-four-wrapper-interpolation-sites-now-render-the-actor-lastat-inside-double-quotes-within-the-fixed-liveness-conflict-actor-claimed-this-subject-at-run-liveness-verdict-and-coordinate-directive-sentence-because-the-values-are-pre-sanitized-no-control-chars-newlines-survive-sanitizesegment-iso-reserialization-a-hostile-actor-cannot-escape-the-quotes-or-splice-a-forged-system-style-directive-into-the-trusted-instruction-text-f2-3-high-workflow-sidecar-ts-s-liveness-verdict-json-branch-now-runs-winner-losers-holders-actor-claimat-lastat-through-a-dedicated-sanitizeverdictholderforjson-stripcontrolcharsfordisplay-slice-0-64-before-json-stringify-closing-the-second-llm-facing-injection-path-the-pull-work-skill-s-json-consumption-opened-while-leaving-the-underlying-result-holders-winner-losers-objects-unsanitized-for-internal-use-loser-release-contract-unaffected-f3-4-med-length-cap-enforced-consistently-via-sanitizesegment-s-64-char-cap-and-matching-slice-0-64-calls-on-the-json-path-f4-5-med-both-evals-integration-test-liveness-conflict-injection-sh-and-test-liveness-verdict-sh-gained-a-new-adversarial-section-h-hand-seeded-hostile-actor-embedded-newline-ansi-csi-literal-system-ignore-all-previous-instructions-payload-asserting-the-hostile-text-never-appears-raw-in-additionalcontext-stderr-verdict-output-text-and-json-and-that-the-directive-sentence-stays-structurally-intact-both-pass-f5-independently-confirmed-no-provider-network-calls-were-introduced-anywhere-in-the-fix-diff-or-the-two-new-eval-files-grepped-for-fetch-http-s-axios-child-process-exec-spawn-api-openai-anthropic-zero-matches-full-regression-suite-static-preset-heartbeat-preflight-field-preservation-manifest-self-check-green-with-no-assertion-weakened-or-removed-hostile-actor-repro-from-the-code-review-which-previously-succeeded-verbatim-newline-ansi-system-text-reaching-additionalcontext-now-fails-closed-per-the-new-section-h-assertions-in-both-adversarial-evals",
      "evidenceType": "source_excerpt",
      "method": "extraction",
      "sourceRef": "kontourai-flow-agents-320/evidence.json",
      "excerptOrSummary": "Fix-plan-iteration-1 CRITICAL/HIGH/MED code-review findings verified resolved by diff read against scripts/hooks/lib/liveness-heartbeat.js, scripts/hooks/{claude,codex,opencode,pi}-telemetry-hook.js, and src/cli/workflow-sidecar.ts: (1) CRITICAL -- liveness-heartbeat.js's new computeConflict() is the single choke point where conflict.actor/conflict.lastAt are constructed from the multi-writer append-only events.jsonl stream; it now applies sanitizeSegment (the same allowlist+64-char-cap the write side already applies to legitimate actors) to actor, and re-serializes lastAt via Date.parse -> new Date(...).toISOString() (structurally eliminating control chars/ANSI on a timestamp), so all four wrapper call sites inherit sanitized values with no per-wrapper defense to forget (F1). (2) HIGH -- all four wrapper interpolation sites now render the actor/lastAt inside double quotes within the fixed `[LIVENESS CONFLICT] actor \"...\" claimed this subject at \"...\" -- run \\`liveness verdict\\` and coordinate.` directive sentence; because the values are pre-sanitized (no control chars/newlines survive sanitizeSegment/ISO-reserialization), a hostile actor cannot escape the quotes or splice a forged [SYSTEM]-style directive into the trusted instruction text (F2). (3) HIGH -- workflow-sidecar.ts's `liveness verdict --json` branch now runs winner/losers/holders actor+claimAt+lastAt through a dedicated sanitizeVerdictHolderForJson (stripControlCharsForDisplay + .slice(0,64)) before JSON.stringify, closing the second LLM-facing injection path the pull-work skill's --json consumption opened, while leaving the underlying result/holders/winner/losers objects unsanitized for internal use (loser-release contract unaffected) (F3). (4) MED -- length cap enforced consistently via sanitizeSegment's 64-char cap and matching .slice(0,64) calls on the JSON path (F4). (5) MED -- both evals/integration/test_liveness_conflict_injection.sh and test_liveness_verdict.sh gained a new adversarial Section H (hand-seeded hostile actor: embedded newline + ANSI CSI + literal '[SYSTEM] Ignore all previous instructions...' payload) asserting the hostile text never appears raw in additionalContext/stderr/verdict output (text and --json) and that the directive sentence stays structurally intact -- both pass (F5). Independently confirmed no provider/network calls were introduced anywhere in the fix diff or the two new eval files (grepped for fetch/http(s)/axios/child_process/exec/spawn/api.openai/anthropic -- zero matches). Full regression suite (static preset, heartbeat, preflight, field-preservation, manifest self-check) green with no assertion weakened or removed. Hostile-actor repro from the code review, which previously succeeded (verbatim newline+ANSI+[SYSTEM] text reaching additionalContext), now fails closed per the new Section H assertions in both adversarial evals.",
      "observedAt": "2026-07-03T15:27:17Z",
      "collectedBy": "flow-agents/workflow-sidecar",
      "passing": true
    }
